                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north base of the central shrine in the Naṭanapādēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 38: 1107-08 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records an undertaking by Bhāradvāji Tirunīlakaṇṭaṉ Tiruvēkambam-uḍaiyāṉ and his brothers Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiyāṉ and Kuṉikkum Pirāṉ, the <hi rend="italic">śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> of the temple of Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram uḍaiya Mahādēva in Śōḻakulavallinallūr in Paṭṭāṉpākkai-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu to burn two <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamps in the temple of the god, one for 1 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> and 6 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> received from Pākkam-uḍaiyāṉ Tillaikkūttaṉ Dēvaṉ and the other for a similar amount received from Taṇḍal-uḍaiyāṉ Panichchai Śāttaṉ.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
